  "prompt": "How do AKC and ACA dog clubs differ?",
  "response": "Here are key differences between AKC and ACA dog registries:\n\nAKC (American Kennel Club):\n- Oldest and most established registry in the United States\n- Recognizes over 190 purebred dog breeds\n- Strict breed standards and lineage requirements\n- More prestigious and widely recognized\n- Focuses on purebred dog breeding and showing\n- Higher registration fees\n- Offers extensive breed-specific competitions and events\n\nACA (American Canine Association):\n- Newer and smaller registry compared to AKC\n- Less stringent breed registration requirements\n- Generally lower registration costs\n- Accepts a broader range of dog breeds and mixed breeds\n- Provides basic registration services\n- Less focused on show competitions\n- More accessible to casual dog owners and breeders\n\nThe primary distinction is that AKC is more rigorous and traditional in its approach, while ACA is more inclusive and flexible in breed registration.",
